rComments: Prof. Matthen ensures that students understand the concepts - his examples and analogies are extremely simple, yet beautifully showcase the complex concepts. Go to class, pay attention, ask questions, and try to truly understand (rather than memorizing) the concepts - and you will for sure do well. I took every course he taught at UTM!

I've worked with professor Matthen on some courses and an individual study. Professor Matthen is brilliant and insightful and does not accept any mediocrity. He is a first grade professor and scholar. He is deeply passionate about the things he cares about and is not afraid to share his opinion on various issues in philosophy.

Professor Matthen's ability to command a lecture is exemplary. Only serious philosophy students should take his courses. You will excel if you know 'how to say the most by saying the least', a challenge unlike any other. His tests are hard and his rubric is harder. He is gentle and generous with his time if he sees your eagerness to learn.
